# Middleware + auth

Three-role auth (PR #21 added receptionist; PR #27 fixed redirect loops + cookie propagation).

## Effective role, not raw role

`profiles.role='therapist'` with `profiles.therapist_id = NULL` is an **internally inconsistent state** — typically a half-completed invite. Middleware must compute the **effective role** via [src/lib/roles.ts](../../src/lib/roles.ts) helpers:

- `getEffectiveRole(profile)` — returns `'therapist'` only when `therapist_id` is also set. Symmetric for receptionist.
- `allowedOrRedirect(effectiveRole, pathname)` — returns `portal | null`. When `null`, the route is allowed; otherwise redirect.
- `portalForRole(effectiveRole)` — `/admin` / `/reception` / `/therapist` / `/login` (no effective role).

Broken-link users stay on `/login` with a `?error=...` banner; they do **not** get redirected into a portal they can't serve.

## Cookie propagation — mandatory

`NextResponse.redirect(url)` creates a fresh response with no `Set-Cookie` headers. If you redirect inside `middleware.ts`, the refreshed Supabase session cookies written by `auth.getUser()` are dropped — and the user's next request will fail auth and bounce back. Use the `redirectWithCookies(url)` helper at every redirect site; it explicitly copies every cookie from `supabaseResponse` onto the redirect before returning.

## Role × portal matrix

Enforced at middleware + covered by [src/lib/__tests__/roles.test.ts](../../src/lib/__tests__/roles.test.ts):

| Role | /admin | /reception | /therapist |
|---|---|---|---|
| `super_admin` | allow | allow (full inbox visibility) | deny → /admin |
| `receptionist` | deny → /reception | allow | deny → /reception |
| `therapist` | deny → /therapist | deny → /therapist | allow |
| unauthenticated | deny → /login | deny → /login | deny → /login |

## Pitfalls

- Don't bypass `getEffectiveRole` by reading `profile.role` directly — you'll reintroduce the loop.
- Don't add a new redirect site without routing it through `redirectWithCookies`.
- The five redirect sites in [src/middleware.ts](../../src/middleware.ts) all go through the helper (lines ~43-94). Grep for `redirectWithCookies` before adding a new one.
